issue.title: Cannot update Business Card: "Error notifying the Peppol Directory to index"
issue.body:
Hi @phax ,

I faced an issue while updating the Business Cards. **I could register new service groups, endpoints and business cards**, but I cannot sync to PEPPOL Directory. 
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/46865258/199664419-d25bee8c-4cd6-4130-bb48-2d3bc8a59cdb.png)

This is my SMP setting:
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/46865258/199664976-44157998-17d1-4cda-8c7d-a069ad373fff.png)

I'm not sure if the endpoint has been successfully registered or not, but after the registration, I could find the records on [Peppol Practical Tool](https://peppol.helger.com/public/locale-en_US/menuitem-tools-participant), but no record on [Peppol Directory](https://directory.peppol.eu/public),

This issue happened after I updated the certificate for both production(SML) and testing(SMK) environments, but the testing instance don't have any issues after that.

Regards,
Alex

comment.body:
Hi @MengXinAlex,
The following possibilities come to my mind:
1. This SMP instance is configured with a Peppol Test (Pilot) certificate and you want to push to the production Directory (directory.peppol.eu). This will not work - please change the settings to use "https://test-directory.peppol.eu" instead.
2. You configured a TLS truststore for the PD client (properties `pdclient.truststore.*` - see https://github.com/phax/phoss-directory/#client-configuration-properties) that does not contain the proper certificates
3. You forget to properly configure the PD client keystore (properties `pdclient.keystore.*` - see also https://github.com/phax/phoss-directory/#client-configuration-properties )

What version of SMP are you running? Did you recently update to a newer version?

hth, Philip

issue.title: Add support for java 8 annotation targets TYPE_USE and TYPE_PARAMETER
issue.body:
Java 8 adds two new targets for annotations.
- TYPE_USE - here are some examples

```
class MyData implements MyTypedInterface<@Limit(2) MyType> {}

new @Immutable Rock()

(@NonNull String) calculateValue()

void doSomething() throws @Critical IOException();

```

For all possible 16 type uses refer to https://docs.oracle.com/javase/specs/jls/se8/html/jls-4.html#jls-4.11
- TYPE_PARAMETER - is for declaring type parameters like

```
class MyClass<@NonNull T> {}

<@Immutable T> void process(T message);
```

comment.body: Yes, feel free to submit a PR - the next update will anyway a major version (4) :)

issue.title: Validate XML Schema for AS4 Receipts

labels.name: issue
labels.description: Issue which are under review, can be bug

issue.body:
Hi guys,
It seems like you are not checking incoming AS4 Receipts against the XML Schema rules.
E.g. a `MessagePartNRInformation` element that contains both a `MessagePartProperties` and a `ds:Reference` element is accepted:
![grafik](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/196219/91693407-459a7580-eb6b-11ea-8a80-68d51653e35e.png)

According to the XML schema this is a choice.
This leeds to non-standard behaviour in the Peppol Testbed.

Thanks and BR,
Philip o.b.o. OpenPEPPOL eDEC

comment.body: Thanks Arun - I this will bring some good improvement to the overall quality on the exchanged messages in the network :)

issue.title: Honour the mandatory "AgreementRef" value in Peppol

labels.name: issue
labels.description: Issue which are under review, can be bug

issue.body:
Hi guys,

The Peppol AS4 specification mandates the usage of the value `urn:fdc:peppol.eu:2017:agreements:tia:ap_provider` for the `AgreementRef` element in AS4 user message. See https://docs.peppol.eu/edelivery/as4/specification/#_agreement for details.

The OpenPEPPOL eDEC CMB now clarified, that messages that don't contain an `AgreementRef` value or messages that contains a different `AgreementRef` value should be rejected. Please adopt this accordingly in Oxalis.

Thanks, Philip o.b.o. OpenPEPPOL eDEC

issue.body:
Hi @phax ,

I faced an issue while updating the Business Cards. **I could register new service groups, endpoints and business cards**, but I cannot sync to PEPPOL Directory. 
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/46865258/199664419-d25bee8c-4cd6-4130-bb48-2d3bc8a59cdb.png)

This is my SMP setting:
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/46865258/199664976-44157998-17d1-4cda-8c7d-a069ad373fff.png)

I'm not sure if the endpoint has been successfully registered or not, but after the registration, I could find the records on [Peppol Practical Tool](https://peppol.helger.com/public/locale-en_US/menuitem-tools-participant), but no record on [Peppol Directory](https://directory.peppol.eu/public),

This issue happened after I updated the certificate for both production(SML) and testing(SMK) environments, but the testing instance don't have any issues after that.

Regards,
Alex

comment.body:
Hi @MengXinAlex,
The following possibilities come to my mind:
1. This SMP instance is configured with a Peppol Test (Pilot) certificate and you want to push to the production Directory (directory.peppol.eu). This will not work - please change the settings to use "https://test-directory.peppol.eu" instead.
2. You configured a TLS truststore for the PD client (properties `pdclient.truststore.*` - see https://github.com/phax/phoss-directory/#client-configuration-properties) that does not contain the proper certificates
3. You forget to properly configure the PD client keystore (properties `pdclient.keystore.*` - see also https://github.com/phax/phoss-directory/#client-configuration-properties )

What version of SMP are you running? Did you recently update to a newer version?

hth, Philip

issue.title: Cannot update Business Card: "Error notifying the Peppol Directory to index"
issue.body:
Hi @phax ,

I faced an issue while updating the Business Cards. **I could register new service groups, endpoints and business cards**, but I cannot sync to PEPPOL Directory. 
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/46865258/199664419-d25bee8c-4cd6-4130-bb48-2d3bc8a59cdb.png)

This is my SMP setting:
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/46865258/199664976-44157998-17d1-4cda-8c7d-a069ad373fff.png)

I'm not sure if the endpoint has been successfully registered or not, but after the registration, I could find the records on [Peppol Practical Tool](https://peppol.helger.com/public/locale-en_US/menuitem-tools-participant), but no record on [Peppol Directory](https://directory.peppol.eu/public),

This issue happened after I updated the certificate for both production(SML) and testing(SMK) environments, but the testing instance don't have any issues after that.

Regards,
Alex

comment.body:
Hi @MengXinAlex,
The following possibilities come to my mind:
1. This SMP instance is configured with a Peppol Test (Pilot) certificate and you want to push to the production Directory (directory.peppol.eu). This will not work - please change the settings to use "https://test-directory.peppol.eu" instead.
2. You configured a TLS truststore for the PD client (properties `pdclient.truststore.*` - see https://github.com/phax/phoss-directory/#client-configuration-properties) that does not contain the proper certificates
3. You forget to properly configure the PD client keystore (properties `pdclient.keystore.*` - see also https://github.com/phax/phoss-directory/#client-configuration-properties )

What version of SMP are you running? Did you recently update to a newer version?

hth, Philip

issue.title: Add support for java 8 annotation targets TYPE_USE and TYPE_PARAMETER
issue.body:
Java 8 adds two new targets for annotations.
- TYPE_USE - here are some examples

```
class MyData implements MyTypedInterface<@Limit(2) MyType> {}

new @Immutable Rock()

(@NonNull String) calculateValue()

void doSomething() throws @Critical IOException();

```

For all possible 16 type uses refer to https://docs.oracle.com/javase/specs/jls/se8/html/jls-4.html#jls-4.11
- TYPE_PARAMETER - is for declaring type parameters like

```
class MyClass<@NonNull T> {}

<@Immutable T> void process(T message);
```

issue.title: Validate XML Schema for AS4 Receipts

labels.name: issue
labels.description: Issue which are under review, can be bug

issue.body:
Hi guys,
It seems like you are not checking incoming AS4 Receipts against the XML Schema rules.
E.g. a `MessagePartNRInformation` element that contains both a `MessagePartProperties` and a `ds:Reference` element is accepted:
![grafik](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/196219/91693407-459a7580-eb6b-11ea-8a80-68d51653e35e.png)

According to the XML schema this is a choice.
This leeds to non-standard behaviour in the Peppol Testbed.

Thanks and BR,
Philip o.b.o. OpenPEPPOL eDEC

comment.body: Thanks Arun - I this will bring some good improvement to the overall quality on the exchanged messages in the network :)

issue.title: Honour the mandatory "AgreementRef" value in Peppol

labels.name: issue
labels.description: Issue which are under review, can be bug

issue.body:
Hi guys,

The Peppol AS4 specification mandates the usage of the value `urn:fdc:peppol.eu:2017:agreements:tia:ap_provider` for the `AgreementRef` element in AS4 user message. See https://docs.peppol.eu/edelivery/as4/specification/#_agreement for details.

The OpenPEPPOL eDEC CMB now clarified, that messages that don't contain an `AgreementRef` value or messages that contains a different `AgreementRef` value should be rejected. Please adopt this accordingly in Oxalis.

Thanks, Philip o.b.o. OpenPEPPOL eDEC
